-- ServiceNow's revenue jumps 67 pct 
-- 
-- Wed Jan 29, 2014 04:48PM EST
-- None



Jan 29 (Reuters) - ServiceNow Inc <NOW.N>, a software company focused on IT infrastructure, reported a 67 percent rise in fourth-quarter revenue as it added more customers, sending its shares up 5 percent in extended trading.

Revenue jumped to $125.2 million in the quarter ended Dec. 31, from $75.2 million a year earlier.